In mathematics, the '''Narumi polynomials''' ''s''<sub>''n''</sub>(''x'') are polynomials introduced by {{harvtxt|Narumi|1929}} given by the [[generating function]]

:<math>\displaystyle \sum s_n(x)t^n/n! = \left(\frac{t}{\log(1+t)}\right)^a(1+t)^x</math>

{{harv|Roman|1984|loc=4.4}}, {{harv|Boas|Buck|1958|loc=p.37}}

